Let's now determine the rate of return of investment to Live Forever Life Insurance Co.'s contract.


$$ \begin{aligned}
r &= \dfrac{\$1,250}{\$254,000}
\\[10pt]
&= {\bf0.51\% }
\end{aligned}$$

**Therefore, the monthly investment return of the perpetuity contract is 0.51%.**

The annual percentage rate can be calculated using the following formula:

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{APR} &=\text{Period}\times\text{Rate}
\end{aligned}$$
